PROMOTE (Admin Command)
=======================

Usage: promote <player> <level>

Change a player's access level.

Arguments:
  <player>  - The username of the player to promote/demote
  <level>   - The new access level: player, wizard, or admin

Examples:
  promote alice wizard       - Make Alice a wizard
  promote bob player         - Demote Bob back to player
  promote charlie admin      - Make Charlie an admin

Access Levels:
  player  - Normal player, can use standard commands
  wizard  - Can use wizard commands (clone, dest, goto, load, ls)
  admin   - Full access including promote and shutdown

Notes:
  - Requires Admin access level
  - Wizards get their own home directory at /wizards/<username>/
  - Be careful when granting admin access

See also: who
